/SUBSECTION Pleased (16-20) SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE We will purge the world of the undead! QUOTE/ 

The shield and its owner are fulfilling the shields goals and it is very pleased.

The Shield's enhancement bonus (when used as a weapon) increases to +4
  /EM Critical: EM/ +4d12 damage or +4d12 radiant damage vs undead and the target is immobilized (save ends).
  /EM Property: EM/ You gain +5 resistance to all necrotic damage.
  /EM Power (Daily): EM/ Burst 5; one undead creature within the burst gains vulnerability 5 to radiant damage until the end of the encounter.
/SUBSECTION Satisfied (12-15) SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE We are a bastion against the undead, let them beware! QUOTE/ 

The wielder has proven himself to be a steadfast enemy of the undead and supporter of the Kingdom of Kinergh.

/EM Property: EM/ You gain +4 to saves vs the effects of attacks made by the undead.
/SUBSECTION Normal (5-11) SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE We must purge the undead from the world and save Kinergh. QUOTE/ 

The shield urges its owner to greater exploits in pursuit of its goals.
/SUBSECTION Unsatisfied (1-4) SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE You have not proven yourself. QUOTE/ 

The shield does not find its owner to be a satisfactory champion. If the wielder does not begin to advance the shield's goals soon it will depart.

/EM Special: EM/ The shield refuses to be wielded against any opponents except the undead and will only use its powers against them.
/SUBSECTION Angered (0 or lower) SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE I must find a true champion, you are not worthy. QUOTE/ 

The wielder has failed to prove his worth and the shield will not remain for long.

/EM Special: EM/ The Sheild's enhancement bonus drops to +1.
/SUBSECTION Moving On SUBSECTION/ 

 /QUOTE Kinergh is safe now from the undead. I must await the next call. QUOTE/ 

The shield has done all it can in the hands of this wielder. It will now return to the treasure horde of the Kings of Kinergh or some other safe place until it is needed again. When the character next gains a level the shield vanishes. If the Shield is at least satisfied it leaves behind a normal Level 13 Sun Shield (heavy shield) for the wielder. If the shield is pleased it grants the wielder the feat Shield Proficiency (heavy shield) as a boon. This boon will last until the wielder gains another feat slot.
